<% content_for(:page_title, 'Admin template style guide') %>

<div class="page-header">
  <h1>
    Admin template style guide
  </h1>
</div>

<p class="lead">Admin app UIs are powered by <a href="http://getbootstrap.com/css/">bootstrap 3.1</a>, using <a href="https://github.com/twbs/bootstrap-sass/tree/v3.1.0">bootstrap SASS</a> v3.1.0 (<a href="https://github.com/twbs/bootstrap-sass/blob/v3.1.0/vendor/assets/stylesheets/bootstrap/_mixins.scss">mixins</a>), but maintaining bootstrap 2 button styles. This guide documents how we use bootstrap, where the apps have diverged from default styles and any custom styles needed to fill in the gaps.</p>

<h2>Grid</h2>
<p class="lead">Apps use the <a href="http://getbootstrap.com/css/#grid">default bootstrap</a> <strong>12 column scaleable responsive grid</strong>.</p>
<div class="row add-bottom-margin">
  <div class="grid-example col-md-2">col-md-2</div>
  <div class="grid-example col-md-4">col-md-4</div>
  <div class="grid-example col-md-6">col-md-6</div>
</div>
<div class="row">
  <div class="grid-example col-md-12">col-md-12</div>
</div>
<hr>

<h2>Input widths</h2>
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-md-6 lead">
    <p>Bootstrap 3 inputs always <a href="http://getbootstrap.com/css/#forms">extend to the size of their container</a>. The recommendation from Bootstrap is to wrap form elements with grid classes. Sometimes this isn’t suitable, for instance if a page isn’t using a grid.</p>
    <p>The gem includes classes to restrict the width of inputs based on column sizes: <code>input-md-x</code> (1 — 11)</p>
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-6">
    <div class="form-group">
      <label>Default input</label>
      <input class="form-control" />
    </div>
    <div class="form-group">
      <label>A short input</label>
      <input class="input-md-2 form-control" value="input-md-2" />
    </div>
    <div class="form-group">
      <label>A longer input</label>
      <input class="input-md-4 form-control" value="input-md-4" />
    </div>
    <div class="form-group">
      <label>Inputs too long will collapse</label>
      <input class="input-md-11 form-control" value="input-md-11" />
    </div>
    <div class="form-group">
      <label>A short select</label>
      <select class="input-md-2 form-control" value="input-md-11">
        <option>Option</option>
      </select>
    </div>
    <div class="form-group form-inline">
      <label>Inline inputs</label><br />
      <input class="input-md-3 form-control add-right-margin" value="input-md-3" />
      <input class="input-md-2 form-control" value="input-md-2" />
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<h3 class="add-bottom-margin">Inputs in a grid</h3>
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-md-1">
    <input class="input-md-1 form-control" value="input-md-1" />
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-2">
    <input class="input-md-2 form-control" value="input-md-2" />
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-3">
    <input class="input-md-3 form-control" value="input-md-3" />
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-6">
    <input class="input-md-6 form-control" value="input-md-6" />
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-4 add-top-margin">
    <input class="input-md-4 form-control" value="input-md-4" />
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-8 add-top-margin">
    <input class="input-md-8 form-control" value="input-md-8" />
  </div>
</div>
<hr>

<h2>Buttons</h2>
<div class="row">
  <p class="col-md-6 lead">Despite using bootstrap 3 apps use the classic bootstrap button styles — the buttons have better affordance and clearer focus and active states. The source to override the buttons with the originals is from <a href="https://gist.github.com/Erve1879/6167373">https://gist.github.com/Erve1879/6167373</a>.</p>
  <div class="col-md-6">
    <a href="#" class="btn btn-default">Default</a>
    <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary">Primary</a>
    <a href="#" class="btn btn-success">Success</a>
    <a href="#" class="btn btn-info">Info</a>
    <a href="#" class="btn btn-warning">Warning</a>
    <a href="#" class="btn btn-danger">Danger</a>
    <a href="#" class="btn btn-link">Link</a>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="row">
  <p class="col-md-6 lead">Create and success actions use <code>btn-success</code>.</p>
  <div class="col-md-6">
    <a href="#" class="btn btn-success">
      Save mapping
    </a>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="row">
  <p class="col-md-6 lead">When adding an item include an <code>icon-plus</code> icon.</p>
  <div class="col-md-6">
    <a href="#" class="btn btn-default">
      <i class="glyphicon glyphicon-plus"></i> Add mapping
    </a>
  </div>
</div>
<hr>

<h2>Dates</h2>
<div class="row">
  <p class="col-md-6 lead">
    The gem includes date and time formats which match the <a href="https://www.gov.uk/design-principles/style-guide/style-points#style-dates-and-times">recommended style</a>.
  </p>
  <section class="col-md-6">
    <h2 class="remove-top-margin">Default</h2>
    <% halloween = Date.new(2013, 10, 31) %>
    <blockquote><%= halloween %><br />
      <%= halloween.to_time %>
    </blockquote>

    <h2>Friendly</h2>
    <blockquote>
      <dl class="remove-bottom-margin">
        <dt class="add-label-margin"><code>:govuk_date</code></dt>
        <dd><%= halloween.to_s(:govuk_date) %><br />
          <%= halloween.to_time.to_s(:govuk_date) %></dd>
        <dt class="add-top-margin add-label-margin"><code>:govuk_date_short</code></dt>
        <dd><%= halloween.to_s(:govuk_date_short) %><br />
          <%= halloween.to_time.to_s(:govuk_date_short) %></dd>
        <dt class="add-top-margin add-label-margin"><code>:govuk_time</code></dt>
        <dd><%= halloween.to_time.to_s(:govuk_time) %></dd>
      </dl>
    </blockquote>
  </section>
</div>
<hr>

<h2>Page headers with subtitles</h2>
<div class="row">
  <p class="col-md-6 lead">Page headers have a single pixel bottom-border. Subtitles - if used - run underneath this.</p>
  <section class="headers col-md-6">
    <header>
      <div class="page-title">
        <h1>
          <span class="small">www.ukspaceagency.com</span>
          UK Space Agency
        </h1>
      </div>
      <p class="subtitle">UKSA is an executive agency of <a href="<%= @normal_link_href %>">BIS</a></p>

      <div class="page-title with-border">
        <h1>
          <span class="small">www.ukspaceagency.com</span>
          UK Space Agency
        </h1>
      </div>
      <p class="subtitle">UKSA is an executive agency of <a href="<%= @normal_link_href %>">BIS</a></p>

    </header>
  </section>
</div>
<hr>

<h2>Tables</h2>
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-md-6 lead">
    <p>When using a table with two layers of headings, usually for interacting with table content, <code>table-header</code> and <code>table-header-secondary</code> classes are used.</p>

    <p>The second example shows a table with selectable rows. Selected rows highlight in yellow. The checkbox in the header selects all rows.</p>
  </div>
  <ul class="col-md-6">
    <table class="table table-bordered table-hover">
      <thead>
        <tr class="table-header">
          <th>Primary header</th>
        </tr>
        <tr class="table-header-secondary">
          <th>Secondary header</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>Typical row</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Typical row</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
    </table>

    <table class="table table-bordered table-hover" data-module="selectable-table">
      <thead>
        <tr class="table-header">
          <th></th>
          <th>Primary header</th>
        </tr>
        <tr class="table-header-secondary">
          <th class="selectable-row">
            <div class="relative">
              <label>
                <input type="checkbox" class="js-toggle-all" />
              </label>
            </div>
          </th>
          <th><a href="<%= @normal_link_href %>" class="btn btn-default">Action</a></th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr class="selected-row">
        <td class="selectable-row">
          <div class="relative">
            <label>
              <input type="checkbox" checked="checked" class="js-toggle-row" />
            </label>
          </div>
        </td>
        <td>Selected row</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td class="selectable-row">
          <div class="relative">
            <label>
              <input type="checkbox" />
            </label>
          </div>
        </td>
        <td>Typical row</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
    </table>
  </ul>
</div>
<hr>

<h2>Links</h2>
<div class="row">
  <div class="col-md-6 lead">
    <p>To match bootstrap’s muted text, a muted link class is available.</p>
    <p>Purple <code>:visited</code> styles have been added. These apply to the main content but not to buttons.</p>
  </div>
  <div class="col-md-6">
    <a href="<%= @normal_link_href %>" class="link-muted">Muted link</a><br><br>
    <a href="<%= @visited_link_href %>">Visited link</a><br><br>
    <a href="<%= @normal_link_href %>">Normal link</a><br><br>
    An <a href="<%= @visited_link_href %>" class="link-inherit">underlined link</a> that inherits its colour<br><br>
    <a href="<%= @visited_link_href %>" class="btn btn-default">Visited button link</a><br><br>
    <a href="<%= @visited_link_href %>" class="btn btn-success">Another visited button link</a><br><br>
  </div>
</div>

